{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "ConcentricTunnel",
  "description": "Concentric polygon rings expanding outward from the centre — fully decomposed onto the curated atom library. The polyline-construction pattern is now visible as graph nodes (TouchDesigner Pattern → Math → Function → Merge shape) rather than sealed inside legacy bundles.\n\nThe instrument organizes into a transparent pipeline. Inputs feeds the top-level IO, Trigger Mode decodes the clip trigger and mode selector into per-behavior gates (shape active, spawn active); those gates select which n-sides value feeds into the polygon outline. Polygon Outline builds a single ring by generating equally-spaced angles, applying cos/sin to get x and y coordinates, and packing them into a curve array. Ring Stack And Render takes that single outline and replicates it into sixteen rings at different scales (based on the expansion envelope and ring spacing), generates the edge topology for the stacked rings using sentinel-safe replication, and renders the final 1024-vertex line set. The groups are purely a presentation layer and flatten to byte-identical behavior at load; card bindings reach inner nodes by stable nodeId regardless of grouping.",
